580: ## Database Patterns
581: 
582: Node.js supports both SQL and NoSQL databases. Use connection pooling for all production databases.
583: 
584: Key patterns covered in [references/advanced-patterns.md](references/advanced-patterns.md):
585: - **PostgreSQL with connection pool** — `pg` Pool configuration and graceful shutdown
586: - **MongoDB with Mongoose** — connection management and schema definition
587: - **Transaction pattern** — `BEGIN`/`COMMIT`/`ROLLBACK` with `pg` client
588: 
589: ## Authentication & Authorization
590: 
591: JWT-based auth with access tokens (short-lived, 15m) and refresh tokens (7d). Full `AuthService` implementation with `bcrypt` password comparison in [references/advanced-patterns.md](references/advanced-patterns.md).
592: 
593: ## Caching Strategies
594: 
595: Redis-backed `CacheService` with get/set/delete/invalidatePattern, plus a `@Cacheable` decorator for method-level caching. See [references/advanced-patterns.md](references/advanced-patterns.md).
596: 
597: ## API Response Format
598: 
599: Standardized `ApiResponse` helper with `success`, `error`, and `paginated` static methods. See [references/advanced-patterns.md](references/advanced-patterns.md).
